<inglise> COMMISSION REGULATION (EC) No 3254/93 of 26 November 1993 laying down detailed rules for the application of Council Regulation (EEC) No 2019/93 as regards the specific supply arrangements for certain fruits and vegetables for the benefit of the smaller Aegean islands </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (EM&Uuml;) nr 3254/93, millega kehtestatakse n&otilde;ukogu m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 2019/93 &uuml;ksikasjalikud rakenduseeskirjad teatavate puu- ja k&ouml;&ouml;giviljade v&auml;iksematele Egeuse mere saartele tarnimise erikorra kohta 26. november 1993 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 2019/93 of 19 July 1993 introducing specific measures for the smaller Aegean islands concerning certain agricultural products (1), and in particular Article 4 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 19. aprilli 1993. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 2019/93, millega kehtestatakse teatavaid p&otilde;llumajandussaadusi k&auml;sitlevad erimeetmed v&auml;iksemate Egeuse mere saarte jaoks, (1) eriti selle artiklit 4, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Commission Regulation (EEC) No 2958/93 (2) lays down common detailed rules for the application of the arrangements for supplying the smaller Aegean islands with certain agricultural products and determines, pursuant to Article 3 (2) of Regulation (EEC) No 2019/93, the amount of the aid for such supply according to the island-group which includes the island in which the product is disposed of; whereas, pursuant to Article 2 of Regulation (EEC) No 2019/93, the smaller Aegean islands' forecast supply balances for fruit and vegetables coming from the rest of the Community should be established for the end of the 1993 calendar year and for the 1994 calendar year; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: komisjoni m&auml;&auml;rus (EM&Uuml;) nr 2958/93 (2) s&auml;testab v&auml;iksematele Egeuse mere saartele teatavate p&otilde;llumajandussaaduste tarnimise korra &uuml;ldised &uuml;ksikasjalikud rakenduseeskirjad ja m&auml;&auml;rab vastavalt m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 2019/93 artikli 3 l&otilde;ikele 2 sellise tarnimise toetuse summa vastavalt saarer&uuml;hmale, kuhu kuulub toodet tarbiv saar; vastavalt m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 2019/93 artiklile 2 tuleks kehtestada v&auml;iksemate Egeuse mere saarte mujalt &uuml;hendusest p&auml;rineva puu- ja k&ouml;&ouml;givilja prognoositav tarnebilanss 1993. kalendriaastaks ja 1994. kalendriaastaks; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in order to attain the objective of the supply arrangements under Regulation (EEC) No 2019/93 and, in particular, to reduce the smaller Aegean islands' natural handicaps without hampering the development potential of local products, it should be made possible for certain fruits and vegetables originating in a smaller island to be covered by the supply arrangements in question, on condition that such basic products are in surplus, relative to that island's specific requirements; whereas, therefore, the amount of the flat-rate aid to be granted for the supply to the smaller islands of the products in question from other smaller islands should be fixed, and the control measures required for the management of such a supply system laid down; </inglise>
<eesti> m&auml;&auml;ruses (EM&Uuml;) nr 2019/93 etten&auml;htud tarnekorra eesm&auml;rgi saavutamiseks ja eriti v&auml;iksemate Egeuse mere saarte ebasoodsate looduslike tingimuste v&auml;hendamiseks, takistamata kohalike toodete v&otilde;imalikku arengut, tuleks v&otilde;imaldada v&auml;ikesaarelt p&auml;rineva teatava puu- ja k&ouml;&ouml;givilja h&otilde;lmamist k&otilde;nealuse tarnekorraga tingimusel, et sellised p&otilde;hitooted on saare konkreetsete vajadustega v&otilde;rreldes &uuml;lej&auml;&auml;k; seet&otilde;ttu tuleks kinnitada kindlasummaline toetus k&otilde;nealuste toodete v&auml;ikesaartele teistelt v&auml;ikesaartelt tarnimiseks ja s&auml;testada sellise tarnes&uuml;steemi haldamiseks vajalikud kontrollmeetmed; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas any fraud should be penalized; </inglise>
<eesti> k&otilde;iki pettusi tuleks karistada; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the provisions of this Regulation should be applied immediately; </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse s&auml;tteid tuleks kohaldada viivitamata; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the opinion of the Management Committee for Fruit and Vegetables, </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses s&auml;testatud meetmed on koosk&otilde;las puu- ja k&ouml;&ouml;giviljaturu korralduskomitee arvamusega, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> For the purposes of Article 2 of Regulation (EEC) No 2019/93, the quantities in the forecast supply balance for fruit and vegetables which are to benefit from Community aid for the end of the 1993 calendar year and for the 1994 calendar year as set out in Annexes I and II to this Regulation. </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 2019/93 artikli 2 kohaldamiseks on 1993. kalendriaasta l&otilde;pus ja 1994. kalendriaastal &uuml;henduse toetust saavad puu- ja k&otilde;&otilde;givilja kogused prognoositavas tarnebilansis ette n&auml;htud k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse I ja II lisas. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> The aid fixed in the first indent of Article 1 (1) of Regulation (EEC) No 2958/93 shall also be granted in respect of: </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 2958/93 artikli 1 l&otilde;ike 1 esimeses taandes kinnitatud toetust antakse samuti j&auml;rgmistele toodetele: </eesti>
<inglise> - mandarins harvested on the island of Khios, up to a maximum quantity of 1 000 tonnes per year, </inglise>
<eesti> - Chiose saarel korjatud mandariinid kuni maksimaalse koguseni 1000 tonni aastas, </eesti>
<inglise> - potatoes for human consumption falling within CN codes 0701 90 51, 0701 90 59 and 0701 90 90 harvested on the island of Naxos, up to a maximum quantity of 3 000 tonnes per year, </inglise>
<eesti> - inimtoiduks m&otilde;eldud CN-koodide 0701 90 51, 0701 90 59 ja 0701 90 90 alla kuuluvad Naxose saarel korjatud kartulid kuni maksimaalse koguseni 3000 tonni aastas, </eesti>
<inglise> - tomatoes harvested on the island of Syros, up to a maximum quantity of 2 000 tonnes per year, </inglise>
<eesti> - Syrose saarel korjatud tomatid kuni maksimaalse koguseni 2000 tonni aastas, </eesti>
<inglise> - courgettes harvested on the island of Syros, up to a maximum quantity of 300 tonnes, </inglise>
<eesti> - Syrose saarel korjatud kabat&scaron;okid kuni maksimaalse koguseni 300 tonni, </eesti>
<inglise> which are dispatched to either of the groups of islands set out in Annexes I and II to that Regulation under the forecast supply balance. </inglise>
<eesti> mis prognoositava tarnebilansi raames saadetakse &uuml;hele selle m&auml;&auml;ruse I ja II lisas loetletud saarer&uuml;hmadest. </eesti>
<inglise> It shall be a condition for benefiting from this provision that the abovementioned products: </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva s&auml;tte kasutamise tingimus on, et eespool nimetatud tooted: </eesti>
<inglise> - shall be in surplus relative to the requirements of the island in which they originate, </inglise>
<eesti> - on &uuml;lej&auml;&auml;gid v&otilde;rreldes nende p&auml;ritolusaare vajadustega, </eesti>
<inglise> - shall have been the subject of a certificate of origin. </inglise>
<eesti> - omavad p&auml;ritolusertifikaati. </eesti>
<inglise> To these ends, the application for the aid certificate and the aid certificate provided for in Article 1 (3) of Regulation (EEC) No 2958/93 shall bear in box 24 the words 'product originating in the island' followed by the name of the smaller island in which the product originates. </inglise>
<eesti> Selleks kantakse abisertifikaadi taotlusele ja m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 2958/93 artikli 1 l&otilde;ikes 3 s&auml;testatud abisertifikaadile lahtrisse 24 s&otilde;nad "toode p&auml;rineb saarelt" koos v&auml;ikesaare nimega, kust toode p&auml;rineb. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> Greece shall designate the competent authority authorized to: </inglise>
<eesti> Kreeka m&auml;&auml;rab p&auml;deva asutuse, kellel on &otilde;igus: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) issue the aid certificate provided for in Article 1 (3) of Regulation (EEC) No 2958/93; </inglise>
<eesti> a) v&auml;ljastada m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 2958/93 artikli 1 l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatud abisertifikaat; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) pay the aid to the operators concerned. </inglise>
<eesti> b) maksta abi asjaomastele ettev&otilde;tjatele. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> An application for a certificate shall be valid only if: </inglise>
<eesti> Sertifikaaditaotlus kehtib ainult juhul, kui: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) the quantity does not exceed the maximum quantity provided for in the supply balance; </inglise>
<eesti> a) kogus ei &uuml;leta tarnebilansis etten&auml;htud suurimat kogust; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) before the deadline set by the competent authorities for the submission of the application for a certificate, proof is supplied that the party concerned has given the security provided for in Article 1 (8) of Regulation (EEC) No 2958/93. </inglise>
<eesti> b) enne p&auml;devate asutuste kehtestatud sertifikaaditaotluste esitamise t&auml;htp&auml;eva t&otilde;endatakse, et asjaomane pool on esitanud m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 2958/93 artikli 1 l&otilde;ikes 8 s&auml;testatud tagatise. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The certificates shall be issued no later than the 15th working day of each month. </inglise>
<eesti> Sertifikaadid v&auml;ljastatakse hiljemalt iga kuu 15. t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eval. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Where the certificates are issued for smaller quantities than those requested, the operator concerned may withdraw his application in writing within three working days of the date of issue of the certificate. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui sertifikaadid antakse taotletust v&auml;iksemale kogusele, v&otilde;ib asjaomane ettev&otilde;tja kolme t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul p&auml;rast sertifikaadi v&auml;ljaandmise kuup&auml;eva oma taotluse kirjalikult tagasi v&otilde;tta. </eesti>
<inglise> The security relating to the certificate shall in such a case be released. </inglise>
<eesti> Sel juhul vabastatakse sertifikaadi tagatis. </eesti>
<inglise> 4. </inglise>
<eesti> 4. </eesti>
<inglise> The maximum quantity available shall be disclosed by the competent authority in the last week of the month preceding that in which the applications are submitted. </inglise>
<eesti> Suurima k&auml;ttesaadava koguse avaldab p&auml;dev asutus taotluste esitamise kuule eelneva kuu viimasel n&auml;dalal. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 5 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 5 </eesti>
<inglise> The period of validity of the aid certificates shall expire on the last day of the second month following that of issue. </inglise>
<eesti> Abisertifikaatide kehtivusaeg l&otilde;peb nende v&auml;ljastamise kuule j&auml;rgneva teise kuu viimasel p&auml;eval. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 6 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 6 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Where aid has been paid without due entitlement, the competent Greek authorities shall recover the amount concerned with interest from the date on which the aid was paid to the date on which it was recovered. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui toetust on makstud p&otilde;hjendamatult, n&otilde;uavad Kreeka p&auml;devad asutused asjakohase summa tagasi koos intressiga alates toetuse maksmise kuup&auml;evast kuni selle tagasisaamise kuup&auml;evani. </eesti>
<inglise> Where fraud occurs, a fine equal to half the amount paid without due entitlement shall also be applied. </inglise>
<eesti> Pettuse korral kohaldatakse lisaks trahvi, mis v&otilde;rdub poolega p&otilde;hjendamatult makstud abi summast. </eesti>
<inglise> The interest rate applied shall be that in force for similar recovery operations under Greek law. </inglise>
<eesti> Kohaldatakse intressim&auml;&auml;ra, mis kehtib Kreeka &otilde;iguses samasuguste sissen&otilde;udmistoimingute suhtes. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The aid recovered and, where appropriate, interest and the fine shall be paid to the disbursing agencies and deducted by them from the expenditure financed by the European Agricultural Guidance and Guarantee Fund in proportion to the Community contribution. </inglise>
<eesti> Tagasisaadud toetus ning vajaduse korral intressid ja trahv makstakse v&auml;ljamakseasutustele, kes arvavad need maha P&otilde;llumajanduse Arendus- ja Tagatisfondi rahastatavatest kuludest v&otilde;rdeliselt &uuml;henduse panusega. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 7 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 7 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the day of its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas avaldamise p&auml;eval. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
